+- [x] [Review][Patch] Numeric prefix inconsistency across `Canonicalize` paths [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Idempotency/HexalithIdempotencyHasher.cs:48, 209, 220, 239`] — four prefix patterns coexist: integer types use `"n:"`, `double` uses `"n:double:"`, `float` uses `"n:float:"`, and `decimal` uses `"decimal:"` (no `n:`). Documented canonical-line grammar (`docs/contract/sdk-generation-and-idempotency-helpers.md`) implies a single `n:` discriminator. Consumers cannot grep `"n:"` to find numeric fields, and parity oracle implementations across SDK/CLI/MCP risk drifting. Normalize to `"n:decimal:"` (or document the asymmetry as load-bearing).
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `_parsedProblemDetails` is NOT thread-safe despite Round 3 claim [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Generation/Program.cs:382-398`] — plain field assignment with no `Lazy<T>`, `Interlocked.CompareExchange`, or `lock`. Two threads reading `ProblemDetails` on the same exception both observe null, both call `ParseProblemDetails`, both store. Use `Lazy<(ProblemDetails?, string?)>` or `Interlocked.CompareExchange` against a reference-typed backing field.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] Documentation vs code mismatch for `BranchRefPolicyRequest.ComputeIdempotencyHash` signature [`docs/contract/sdk-generation-and-idempotency-helpers.md:69` vs `src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Generated/HexalithFoldersIdempotencyHelpers.g.cs:168`] — doc says "now takes (folderId, repositoryBindingId)" but the generated method is `ComputeIdempotencyHash(string folderId)`; `repositoryBindingId` is sourced from the `RepositoryBindingId` DTO property, not a parameter. Either reword the doc bullet or surface `repositoryBindingId` as a parameter.
