+- [x] [Review][Patch] `EnsureParameter` discards the spine parameter name [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Generation/Program.cs:157-162`] — `if (operationParameters.TryGetValue(field, out string? parameterName)) { _ = parameterName; ... }` fetches the spine's authoritative name and explicitly discards it, then `EnsureParameter` rebuilds the name from `field` via `ToParameterName`. Round 3 Decision D3 said either drop the parameter or use it for spine-to-method name verification. Either (a) pass `parameterName` into `EnsureParameter` and assert `ToParameterName(field) == parameterName` (fail-closed on drift), or (b) drop the lookup since it's unused.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `RejectControlCharacters` only guards `operationId` and `field.Path`, not field values [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Idempotency/HexalithIdempotencyHasher.cs:17, 185` vs `155-156`] — control characters in values fall through to `Escape()` which escapes them rather than rejecting. The idempotency-encoding corpus declares `malformed-idempotency-key-control-character` as `parser-rejected` but the hasher accepts the input as a value. Either reject in `Escape` too, or update the corpus classification to `accepted-with-escape` and align the test.
